The Engineers Board of Kenya (EBK) is a statutory body established under Section 3(1) of the Engineers Act 2011. The Board has the overall mandate of developing and regulating engineering practice in Kenya.The development and regulation of engineering practice is considered a key component to the achievement of infrastructure foundation under the country s Vision 2030 development blueprint.The board is in the process of automating its business processes which will enhance service delivery to clients. See the notice below.